Redeem(address,address,string,bytes).details: Emitted when a pending token is redeemed in the lazy-minting protocol.

constructor.details: Create a new TaureumNFTLazyMint contract and and assign `DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, MINTER_ROLE` for the creator. This construction function should be called from an exchange.

params.to: The address that will own the minted NFT.
params.uri: The URI consists of metadata description of the minting NFT on the IPFS (without prefix).

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

redeem(address,string,bytes).details: Implement a lazy minting mechanism in which the NFT-minting process is delayed until the first order is successful. This function should be handled by a smart contract which is allowed by the `minter`.

params.redeemer: The address that the minted NFT will be transferred to.
params.signature: The signature signed by `to` designating `msg.sender` to mint the NFT for it.
params.uri: The URI consists of metadata description of the minting NFT on the IPFS (without prefix).

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.to: The address that will own the minted NFT.
params.uri: The URI consists of metadata description of the minting NFT on the IPFS (without prefix).

setBaseURI(string).details: Sets new value for the `__baseURI`. This operation can only been done by the owner of this contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

mint(address,string).notice: It throws an exception if    - `to` is a "ZERO_ADDRESS.

redeem(address,string,bytes).notice: It throws if      - `msg.sender` is not the `minter` or has not been approved by the `minter`.      - redeem data and signature are not valid.      - if the redeemer is a contract and it cannot receive the NFT.

safeMint(address,string).notice: It throws an exception if    - `to` is a "ZERO_ADDRESS.    - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon a safe transfer.
